OL,3,CFinal preparations: Choreographing the
OL,4,CKing's visit to the US
OL,6,FThere is one phrase you are unlikely
OL,7,Fto hear pass the lips of senior
OL,8,FBritish diplomats during King Charles'
OL,9,Fvisit next week: "the special
OL,10,Frelationship".
OL,12,FThe creaking cliche coined by Sir
OL,13,FWinston Churchill 80 years ago is seen
OL,14,Fas outdated, overused, and needy.
OL,16,FInstead, the royal visit will be a
OL,17,Fchance to emphasise the deep ties that
OL,18,Fhave bound the United Kingdom and the
OL,19,FUnited States since its Declaration of
OL,20,FIndependence 250 years ago.
OL,26,@qD@ROUrD@MO]
