OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777057867
OL,3,CFinal preparations: Choreographing the
OL,4,CKing's visit to the US
OL,6,FThe King will speak for some 20
OL,7,Fminutes in Congress. He will be only
OL,8,Fthe second British Monarch to ever do
OL,9,Fso (Queen Elizabeth II was the first
OL,10,Fin 1991 during a state visit following
OL,11,Fthe Gulf War). King Charles' speech at
OL,12,Fthe White House will be about 10
OL,13,Fminutes long. Both are being
OL,14,Frepeatedly finessed and rewritten,
OL,15,Fwith one source joking it is on "draft
OL,16,F49" now.
OL,18,FThere is, of course, one unpredictable
OL,19,Ffactor in all these carefully
OL,20,Fchoreographed events, and that is
OL,21,FPresident Trump himself.
OL,26,@wD@aOUxD@CO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
